Of course, the Archdeacon of Oornwall must have been greatly puzzled when he received this Mandate3 for both he and his official, and the Vicar of Tywardreath, knew that every statement con- tained in it was groundless, and that apparently an attempt had been made to take advantage of the Archbishop's ignorance of the locality and of the circumstances of the case. There can be no doubt that, as in duty bound, he lost no time in reporting the matter to his Diocesan, who immediately intel-vened, and endea- voured to quash the proceedings by exposing the fraud.
